  "text": "If object B is perceived as moving of its own accord, could the findings for the separating motion stimulus be explained by models of perception of motion as animate? Several accounts of motion properties leading to perception of animate motion have been proposed ( Feldman 2000, 2006) . None of these, however, has postulated or reported evidence for impressions of animate motion occurring for an object that starts to move when contacted by another object. Indeed, [CITATION_1] proposed that motion onset without contact from another object was a key criterion for identifying motion as animate. None of these accounts, therefore, can explain the present results.",
